  "texts": [
    "If the recommendation is bad, the explanation could be useful for the user to detect the inability of the RS for creating a quality recommendation.",
    "In our case, we consider two levels of explanation: a global level that attempts to provide a general idea of why the entire set of journals was recommended, and a local level, where the explanations focus on each specific recommended journal.",
    "The two explanation elements (EE) considered in this level can be articulated in the following way.",
    "The original output of our recommender system was a list of journals, as depicted in Fig. 1.",
    "However, from the end user's perspective, it can be challenging to discern why a particular journal is ranked higher or lower than others and to what extent."
  ]
}